# Zapocalypse (Cursor)

Treat **`CLAUDE.md`** at the repository root as the **binding** project brief. It pulls in `AGENTS.md`, `.claude/rules/`, and documents skills, slash-command workflows, wiki-first lookup, and memory sync.

- Do **not** maintain Cursor-only copies of those rules; Cursor, Claude Code, and Gemini share `.claude/`.
- **`GEMINI.md`** at the repo root describes the same tri-agent setup from Gemini Antigravity’s perspective.
- When a “slash command” applies, follow the checklist in the matching file under `.claude/commands/` (Cursor has no native `/command` menu for these).
- Run the **Rule 3 memory sync** (`CLAUDE.md` + `.claude/memory/sync-checklist.md`) only **after the user confirms the current work is functioning** — not proactively before commits.
